Macula mesh fork (github.com/rgfaber/Spartan)

Fork of the above by Raf Lefever, to run Spartan entities over the Macula
mesh as hecate-spartan federation members. All original credit remains with
Dr. Gene Sher; these changes are offered back under the same Apache-2.0.

Changes:
- spartan.py: added GroqProvider (OpenAI-compatible Groq backend) + factory
  registration. No existing provider changed.
- spartan_config.yaml: added a `groq_llama` backend (active); set the active
  embedder to the Ollama option so the embedding model runs in a separate
  Ollama sidecar and the container stays lean (LanceDB embedded, no torch).
- Tools/SpartanRadio.py: replaced with a mesh drop-in (identical CLI) routing
  outbound comms to a hecate-spartan node instead of file-write / SCP.
- Tools/macula_radio.py: added — the inbound bridge (mesh inbox -> alerts/).
- Containerfile, entrypoint.sh, .dockerignore: added — headless container
  running the inbound bridge + `spartan.py --headless`.